reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 20, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This is a great keyboard and mouse combo with a number bad! I used it for my promethean board at school. Having just the one USB for both is super convenient. Would highly recommend and buy again. Also love the color!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 3, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I got tired of having so many cords and wanted to find a cute, quiet, and non-bulky keyboard and mouse set. Keyboard is nice and quiet. I've received compliments from all my office mates. I really like the calculator function button on the upper right corner. Definitely would recommend this set.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Worked but broke but happy ending
reviews.reviewText: UPDATE FROM ORIGINAL:After I wrote the review from below, the seller sent me a message and wanted to give me a full refund. I mentioned that I really love the keyboard and I just want one that works so they sent me a replacement. I brought it to work and works great. I am very happy with the seller for wanting to solve the issue and resending a replacement. I offered to send the one that broke back so they could see what happened to it and they said no need. I love this keyboard and mouse. I ordered a new one after this one broke and I did like my new one (from a different vendor) but the mouse was tiny and very sensitive. I really enjoy this one and am glad they sent a replacement for me. Highly recommend this keyboard and customer service is on point!Old review:So this worked fine and then I come into work one day and it wouldn’t do anything. I put new batteries in and the light flickered but then it turned off, the keyboard won’t turn on at all and I’m confused. It was great for the month and now it’s not working. I didn’t do anything different so I just think it’s odd. If it was the battery life, I think it should’ve lasted longer than a month but even if the batteries died, why did everything stop working? Is there a way to refresh the keyboard or something??? I turned it off and back on a few times but only a faint light on the mouse went on and then it powered off and won’t work. How do I go about fixing this?

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 11, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I had one of those bubble, high set key keyboards that LOOKS great but I couldn't type on it to save my life because of the space between the high, round keys, my fingers were constantly tripped up. I honestly don't know how people type on them because I was horrible at it. I needed flatter keys but I need a decent "click" or at least one I could feel. I don't like silent keyboards.This keyboard if the perfect combo. It's super comfortable, it has enough of a click (it's a muted click, if that means anything) and it actually fits on my very shallow pull out keyboard tray. The mouse that comes with it is also a perfectly fine, basic mouse that I really appreciate for it's simplicity.Less is more.My ONLY very tiny gripe is the sleep mode. I wish it just stayed awake. I'm used to it now but I hated having to double click to wake it up at first. That's not enough of one to take more than 1 star away to me but to get 5, you have to be perfect. This one isn't, but it's very close!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars LAGS!! Not ideal for work
reviews.reviewText: Very cute and comfortable. Lightweight, affordable, all of the things you want in a keyboard! EXCEPT it lags so bad. It was fine for a week at work with no issues. The next week, it lagged for a few minutes at a time. Now (3 weeks later) the keyboard doesn't work properly. I'll type a letter in and once it decides to type, it'll have it put in 4 times. The copy and paste function isn't working. The lag is atrocious. I had to switched to a wired keyboard just to do my job well.Unsure if I want to risk trying a replacement or just getting a refund.UPDATE** I got the replacement and started using it today. It is also lagging. If you work in a call center or a job that requires a lot of typing, definitely do not recommend. It would probably be good for leisure.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Mouse does not work well
reviews.reviewText: I really like the keyboard. I got the pink one and I really like the color. I like how quiet the keys are and how well they work. What I don't like is the mouse. It "freezes," for lack of a better word. I'll be scrolling or trying to move it around the screen and the cursor will freeze. I just have to wait for it to start working again. Pretty annoying.
Overall very pleased with the product and I'm glad I didn't need to spend $100 for a keyboard! Would highly recommend for anyone with looking to set up their home office.
